<subSubSection pageId="49" pageNumber="50" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="49.[151,1437,151,1653]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,151,176]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Description.</emphasis>
Erect, massive, stipitate sponge, 70 × 70 × 
<quantity box="[846,926,152,176]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" unit="mm" value="30.0">30 mm</quantity>
diameter (
<figureCitation box="[1049,1155,151,176]" captionStart="FIGURE 20" captionStartId="48.[151,250,1984,2006]" captionTargetBox="[150,1436,301,1963]" captionTargetId="figure@48.[150,1436,301,1963]" captionTargetPageId="48" captionText="FIGURE 20. Phakellia rubra sp. nov. A. In situ; B. Skeletal architecture (B, x5); C. Strongyles (sinuous); D. Style; E. Oxeas; F. Oxeas with hastate modifications" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2651490/files/figure.png" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Fig. 20A</figureCitation>
). Surface smooth, fleshy and conulose, with a skin-like dermal membrane stretched between the ends of the fibres (lost in preservative). Oscules, 
<quantity box="[255,350,223,248]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.5" metricValueMax="5.0" metricValueMin="4.0" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" unit="mm" value="4.5" valueMax="5.0" valueMin="4.0">4–5 mm</quantity>
diameter, sunken on the surface. Ostia, &lt;
<quantity box="[833,900,224,248]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" unit="mm" value="1.0">1 mm</quantity>
diameter spread all over surface. Texture firm, flexible, compressible. Colour in life dark-red; in preservative, beige.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="49.[151,1437,151,1653]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,302,295,320]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Skeleton</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[319,422,295,320]" captionStart="FIGURE 20" captionStartId="48.[151,250,1984,2006]" captionTargetBox="[150,1436,301,1963]" captionTargetId="figure@48.[150,1436,301,1963]" captionTargetPageId="48" captionText="FIGURE 20. Phakellia rubra sp. nov. A. In situ; B. Skeletal architecture (B, x5); C. Strongyles (sinuous); D. Style; E. Oxeas; F. Oxeas with hastate modifications" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2651490/files/figure.png" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Fig. 20B</figureCitation>
). Choanosomal skeleton consists of a dense interwoven mass of sinuous strongyles and styles. Axial spicules disposed longitudinally in a dendritic fashion. Spicule tracts definable for very short distance in choanosome before becoming obscured. Choanosomal peripheral region not well formed; spicules predominantly styles and oxeas, arranged individually, branching tangentially from the axis becoming plumoreticulate and protrude through the ectosome. Styles in the axial and peripheral skeleton do not appear to be differentiated, overlying the axial strongyles. Specialized ectosomal skeleton absent.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="49.[151,1437,151,1653]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,459,511,536]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Spicules. Megascleres</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[476,559,511,536]" captionStart="FIGURE 20" captionStartId="48.[151,250,1984,2006]" captionTargetBox="[150,1436,301,1963]" captionTargetId="figure@48.[150,1436,301,1963]" captionTargetPageId="48" captionText="FIGURE 20. Phakellia rubra sp. nov. A. In situ; B. Skeletal architecture (B, x5); C. Strongyles (sinuous); D. Style; E. Oxeas; F. Oxeas with hastate modifications" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2651490/files/figure.png" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Fig. 20</figureCitation>
C–F). Strongyles, sinuous, occasional stylote modifications occur, 901 (895– 911) × 3 (3) µm, n = 10. Styles, usually slightly curved one-third the distance from the head; some distinctly curved midway, 527 (521–532) × 7 (7) µm, n = 10. Oxeas, slightly curved midway, with one end hastate, 389 (384–392) × 6 (6) µm, n = 10. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[349,500,620,645]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Microscleres</emphasis>
. Absent.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="49.[151,1437,151,1653]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,654,655,680]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Substratum, depth range and ecology.</emphasis>
Found usually on coral rubble, in sheltered locations and rock ledges at a depth of 
<specimenCount box="[297,361,692,716]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" type="generic">
<quantity box="[297,357,692,716]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" unit="m" value="20.0">20 m</quantity>
.
</specimenCount>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="49.[151,1437,151,1653]" box="[199,987,727,752]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,516,727,752]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Geographical distribution.</emphasis>
Sodwana Bay, east coast of 
<collectingCountry box="[836,983,727,752]" name="South Africa" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">South Africa</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,1174,764,789]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="49.[151,1437,151,1653]" box="[199,1174,764,789]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,764,789]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Etymology.</emphasis>
Named for the dark red colour of the sponge (
<emphasis box="[854,917,764,789]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">ruber</emphasis>
meaning dark red, L.).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="49" pageNumber="50" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="49.[151,1437,151,1653]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,799,824]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bowerbank" authorityYear="1862" box="[322,430,799,824]" class="Demospongiae" family="Axinellidae" genus="Phakellia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Halichondrida" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" phylum="Porifera" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[322,430,799,824]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Phakellia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to, and often confused with, 
<taxonomicName box="[869,990,799,824]" class="Demospongiae" family="Dictyonellidae" genus="Acanthella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Halichondrida" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" phylum="Porifera" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[869,990,799,824]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Acanthella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
due to the presence of sinuous spicules in the choanosome. They differ primarily in the arrangement of the choanosomal skeleton (
<bibRefCitation author="Alvarez" box="[1197,1424,836,861]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Alvarez" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" pagination="1 - 47" refId="ref40798" refString="Alvarez, B., Soest, R. W. M. van &amp; Rutzler, K. (1998) A Revision of Axinellidae (Porifera: Demospongiae) in the Central West Atlantic Region. Smithsonian Contributions to Zoology, 598, 1 - 47. https: // doi. org / 10.5479 / si. 00810282.598" type="journal article" year="1998">
Alvarez 
<emphasis box="[1296,1348,836,861]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">et al</emphasis>
. 1998
</bibRefCitation>
). Members of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bowerbank" authorityYear="1862" box="[302,409,871,896]" class="Demospongiae" family="Axinellidae" genus="Phakellia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Halichondrida" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" phylum="Porifera" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[302,409,871,896]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Phakellia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have a well-defined axial region and an extra-axial skeleton and a reticulate peripheral skeleton (
<bibRefCitation author="Bergquist" box="[261,440,908,933]" firstAuthor="Bergquist" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" pagination="1 - 85" refId="ref41305" refString="Bergquist, P. R. (1970) The Marine Fauna of New Zealand: Porifera, Demospongiae, Part 2 (Axinellida and Halichondrida). New Zealand Department of Scientific and Industrial Research Bulletin, New Zealand Oceanographic Institute Memoir 51, 197, 1 - 85." type="journal article" year="1970">Bergquist 1970</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Carvalho" box="[452,690,908,933]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Carvalho" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" pagination="109 - 116" refId="ref42335" refString="Carvalho, M. S., Desqueyroux-Faundez, R. &amp; Hajdu, E. (2007) Phakellia sur sp. nov. (Demospongiae, Halichondrida, Axinellidae) from the lower slope off Cape Horn (South America), with a revision of the genus. Marine Biology Research, 3, 109 - 116. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 17451000701276063" type="journal article" year="2007">
Carvalho 
<emphasis box="[564,615,908,933]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">et al</emphasis>
. 2007
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Alvarez &amp; Hooper" box="[703,986,908,933]" firstAuthor="Alvarez" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" pagination="17 - 42" refId="ref40964" refString="Alvarez, B. &amp; Hooper, J. N. A. (2009) Taxonomic revision of the order Halichondrida (Porifera: Demospongiae) from northern Australia. Family Axinellidae. The Beagle, Records of the Museums and Art Galleries of the Northern Territory, 25, 17 - 42." type="journal article" year="2009">Alvarez &amp; Hooper 2009</bibRefCitation>
). Members of 
<taxonomicName box="[1153,1274,908,933]" class="Demospongiae" family="Dictyonellidae" genus="Acanthella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Halichondrida" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" phylum="Porifera" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1153,1274,908,933]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Acanthella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
lack the axial and extra-axial skeleton, and have a central axial column producing a dendritic skeleton of branching spicule tracts (
<bibRefCitation author="Hooper &amp; Levi" box="[158,398,980,1005]" firstAuthor="Hooper" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" pagination="191 - 212" refId="ref45284" refString="Hooper, J. N. A. &amp; Levi, C. (1994) Biogeography of Indo-west Pacific sponges: Microcionidae, Raspailiidae, Axinellidae. In: Soest, R. W. M. van, Kempen, T. M. G. van &amp; Braekman, J. C. (Eds.), Sponges in Time and Space. Balkema, Rotterdam, pp. 191 - 212." type="book chapter" year="1994">Hooper &amp; Levi 1994</bibRefCitation>
). This species clearly fits within the definition of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bowerbank" authorityYear="1862" box="[952,1059,980,1005]" class="Demospongiae" family="Axinellidae" genus="Phakellia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Halichondrida" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" phylum="Porifera" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[952,1059,980,1005]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Phakellia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Carvalho" box="[1074,1307,980,1005]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Carvalho" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" pagination="109 - 116" refId="ref42335" refString="Carvalho, M. S., Desqueyroux-Faundez, R. &amp; Hajdu, E. (2007) Phakellia sur sp. nov. (Demospongiae, Halichondrida, Axinellidae) from the lower slope off Cape Horn (South America), with a revision of the genus. Marine Biology Research, 3, 109 - 116. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 17451000701276063" type="journal article" year="2007">
Carvalho 
<emphasis box="[1185,1234,980,1005]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">et al</emphasis>
. 2007
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Alvarez &amp; Hooper" firstAuthor="Alvarez" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" pagination="17 - 42" refId="ref40964" refString="Alvarez, B. &amp; Hooper, J. N. A. (2009) Taxonomic revision of the order Halichondrida (Porifera: Demospongiae) from northern Australia. Family Axinellidae. The Beagle, Records of the Museums and Art Galleries of the Northern Territory, 25, 17 - 42." type="journal article" year="2009">Alvarez &amp; Hooper 2009</bibRefCitation>
). The majority of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bowerbank" authorityYear="1862" box="[509,617,1015,1040]" class="Demospongiae" family="Axinellidae" genus="Phakellia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Halichondrida" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" phylum="Porifera" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[509,617,1015,1040]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Phakellia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species are described from all over the world and the genus contains 32 valid of which two are described from the WIO (Van 
<bibRefCitation author="Soest" box="[753,946,1052,1077]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Soest" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" refId="ref50982" refString="Soest, R. W. M Van, Boury-Esnault, N., Hooper, J. N. A., Rutzler, K., de Voogd, N. J., Alvarez, B., Hajdu, E., Pisera, A. B., Manconi, R., Schonberg, C., Klautau, M., Picton, B., Kelly, M., Vacelet, J., Dohrmann, M., Diaz, M. C., Cardenas, P., Carballo, J. L., Rios, P. &amp; Downey, R. (2017) World Porifera database. Available from: http: // www. marinespecies. org / porifera (accessed 5 December 2017)" type="url" year="2017">
Soest 
<emphasis box="[821,878,1052,1077]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">et al.</emphasis>
2017
</bibRefCitation>
). This is the first record of this genus in the South African region. 
<taxonomicName authority="(Dendy, 1916)" authorityName="Dendy" authorityYear="1916" baseAuthorityName="Dendy" baseAuthorityYear="1916" box="[406,779,1087,1112]" class="Demospongiae" family="Axinellidae" genus="Phakellia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Halichondrida" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="radiata">
<emphasis box="[406,606,1087,1112]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Phakellia radiata</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Dendy" box="[621,772,1087,1112]" firstAuthor="Dendy" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" pagination="93 - 146" refId="ref43189" refString="Dendy, A. (1916) Report on the non-Calcareous sponges collected by Mr. James Hornell at Okhamandal in Kattiawar in 1905 - 6. Report to the government of Baroda on the marine zoology of Okhamandal in Kattiawar, 2, 93 - 146, pls. I-IV." type="journal article" year="1916">Dendy, 1916</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, described by 
<bibRefCitation author="Dendy" box="[946,1097,1087,1112]" firstAuthor="Dendy" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" pagination="93 - 146" refId="ref43189" refString="Dendy, A. (1916) Report on the non-Calcareous sponges collected by Mr. James Hornell at Okhamandal in Kattiawar in 1905 - 6. Report to the government of Baroda on the marine zoology of Okhamandal in Kattiawar, 2, 93 - 146, pls. I-IV." type="journal article" year="1916">Dendy (1916</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Dendy" box="[1110,1170,1088,1112]" firstAuthor="Dendy" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" pagination="1 - 164" refId="ref43241" refString="Dendy, A. (1922) Report on the Sigmatotetraxonida collected by H. M. S. ' Sealark' in the Indian Ocean. In: Reports of the Percy Sladen Trust Expedition to the Indian Ocean in 1905. Fol. 7. Transactions of the Linnean Society of London, Series 2, 18 (1), pp. 1 - 164, pls. 1 - 18." type="journal article" year="1922">1922</bibRefCitation>
), is a thin crust (with a large large number of independent but closely located conules on the surface) and differs from the new species in having a dull orange colouration and the presence of trichodragmata. Comparison of spicules dimensions indicates that 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Dendy" baseAuthorityYear="1916" box="[200,311,1196,1221]" class="Demospongiae" family="Axinellidae" genus="Phakellia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Halichondrida" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="radiata">
<emphasis box="[200,311,1196,1221]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">P. radiata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has smaller styles (600 × 
<quantity box="[604,678,1196,1220]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.3" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" unit="mm" value="23.0">23 µm</quantity>
) and strongyles (430 × 
<quantity box="[944,1019,1196,1220]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.7" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" unit="mm" value="17.0">17 µm</quantity>
) and a skeleton of spicule tracts with a reticulation of rounded meshes. 
<bibRefCitation author="Lamarck" box="[558,745,1231,1256]" firstAuthor="Lamarck" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" pagination="294 - 312" refId="ref46136" refString="Lamarck, J. B. P. de M. C. de (1814 [1813]) Sur les polypiers empates. Annales du Museum national d'Histoire naturelle, 1814, 294 - 312 + 370 - 386 + 432 - 458." type="journal article" year="1814">Lamarck (1814)</bibRefCitation>
described 
<taxonomicName authority="(Lamarck, 1814)" authorityName="Lamarck" authorityYear="1814" baseAuthorityName="Lamarck" baseAuthorityYear="1814" box="[878,1215,1231,1256]" class="Demospongiae" family="Axinellidae" genus="Phakellia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Halichondrida" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="labellum">
<emphasis box="[878,1009,1231,1256]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">P. labellum</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Lamarck" box="[1029,1207,1231,1256]" firstAuthor="Lamarck" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" pagination="294 - 312" refId="ref46136" refString="Lamarck, J. B. P. de M. C. de (1814 [1813]) Sur les polypiers empates. Annales du Museum national d'Histoire naturelle, 1814, 294 - 312 + 370 - 386 + 432 - 458." type="journal article" year="1814">Lamarck, 1814</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[1295,1433,1231,1256]" name="Madagascar" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Madagascar</collectingCountry>
. 
<taxonomicName authority="Samaai &amp; Pillay &amp; Janson, 2019" authorityName="Samaai &amp; Pillay &amp; Janson" authorityYear="2019" box="[151,333,1268,1293]" class="Demospongiae" family="Axinellidae" genus="Phakellia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Halichondrida" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="rubra" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[151,333,1268,1293]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Phakellia rubra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[343,437,1268,1293]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[343,437,1268,1293]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
has a similar spicule complement to 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Lamarck" baseAuthorityYear="1814" box="[878,1007,1268,1293]" class="Demospongiae" family="Axinellidae" genus="Phakellia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Halichondrida" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="labellum">
<emphasis box="[878,1007,1268,1293]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">P. labellum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but differs in spicule geometry with having two size categories of styles and in that the strongyles are reduced to very thin and sinuous stylesstrongyles. 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Lamarck" baseAuthorityYear="1814" box="[288,508,1340,1365]" class="Demospongiae" family="Axinellidae" genus="Phakellia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Halichondrida" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="labellum">
<emphasis box="[288,508,1340,1365]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Phakellia labellum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has not since been recorded from 
<collectingCountry box="[946,1081,1340,1365]" name="Madagascar" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Madagascar</collectingCountry>
even though 
<bibRefCitation author="Thomas, P. A." box="[1256,1436,1340,1365]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" pagination="10 - 16" refId="ref51663" refString="Thomas, P. A. (1979 a) Demospongiae of Minicoy Island (Indian Ocean) Part 1 - orders Keratosida and Haplosclerida. Journal of the Marine Biological Association of India, 21 (1 - 2), 10 - 16." type="journal article" year="1979">Thomas (1979)</bibRefCitation>
produced an extensive sponge monograph from this region. Based on the morphological differences between all three species, and the limited distribution potential of sponges, 
<taxonomicName authority="Samaai &amp; Pillay &amp; Janson, 2019" authorityName="Samaai &amp; Pillay &amp; Janson" authorityYear="2019" box="[860,952,1412,1437]" class="Demospongiae" family="Axinellidae" genus="Phakellia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Halichondrida" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="rubra" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[860,952,1412,1437]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">P. rubra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[959,1048,1412,1437]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[959,1048,1412,1437]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
is considered as a new member of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bowerbank" authorityYear="1862" box="[151,258,1447,1472]" class="Demospongiae" family="Axinellidae" genus="Phakellia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Halichondrida" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" phylum="Porifera" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,258,1447,1472]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Phakellia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="49" pageNumber="50" type="key">
<paragraph blockId="49.[151,1437,151,1653]" box="[199,515,1484,1509]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,515,1484,1509]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Key diagnostic characters.</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="49.[151,1437,151,1653]" box="[199,577,1519,1544]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">• Sponge massive and stipitate.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="49" pageNumber="50" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="49.[151,1437,151,1653]" box="[199,428,1556,1581]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">• Dark red colour.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="49.[151,1437,151,1653]" box="[199,1101,1591,1616]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">• Axial spicules disposed longitudinally in a dendritic fashion in choanosome.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="49.[151,1437,151,1653]" box="[199,783,1628,1653]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">• Strongyles, styles and oxeas present as spicules.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
